<section id="about">
  <hr class="divider" />
  <div class="container about-inner">
    <div class="about-left">
      <p class="section-label">About</p>
      <h2>Architect of<br />Moving Images</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-right">
      <p>
        I'm Laura Alvarez — a director and VFX compositor with roots in architecture.
        My training in spatial design shapes how I think about every frame: as a built
        environment, a constructed reality with its own logic, light, and weight.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the VFX pipeline I work at the intersection of live-action and digital
        worlds, compositing elements that feel as grounded and tactile as physical
        spaces. As a director, I bring that same rigor to storytelling — precise,
        considered, and deeply visual.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm drawn to projects that demand both technical depth and creative vision:
        short films, commercials, title sequences, and visual effects for narrative work.
      </p>

      <ul class="skills">
        <li>Direction</li>
        <li>VFX Compositing</li>
        <li>Architectural Visualization</li>
        <li>Nuke</li>
        <li>After Effects</li>
        <li>Pre-production &amp; Concept</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .about-right p {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .about-right p:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .skills {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .skills li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
